| Design direction fit for industry | 10/10 | #0D0D0D bg / #F5F3EF warm white / #C9A96E antique gold palette is precision-calibrated for elite boutique law. Cormorant Garamond (Didone/transitional) + Inter: editorial institutional. Motion vocabulary (stillness, no bounce/spring) is correct. Gibson Dunn / Quinn Emanuel nav + hero + publications patterns confirmed. No portfolio palette bleed. |

**Weighted overall: 42/50 (84%) — PASS threshold: ≥70%**

## Issues (non-blocking — pass to demo-builder as constraints)

1. **WebLLM CDN import in Angular build**: `import * as webllm from "https://esm.run/@mlc-ai/web-llm"` will not resolve in the Angular CLI bundle. CDN import MUST live inside `webllm-worker.js` only (not in `ai-agent.service.ts`). Service communicates with worker via `postMessage`. Demo-builder must implement this correctly.

2. **`webllm-worker.js` missing from file budget**: This is a required 13th file. Not a budget violation (budget says "meaningful hand-crafted files" and it is one), just needs to be acknowledged.

3. **FR locale scope**: French = UI strings only (`assets/i18n/fr.json`), no backend content rows. Nav toggle shows EN/ES/FR but clicking FR will not switch practice-area or publication content — only UI chrome. Demo-builder must show a "Content not yet available in French" graceful state, or scope FR toggle to UI-only with a visible note.

4. **Seed email clarification**: `editor@soloaw.demo` flagged as likely typo in plan-gate; plan-gate defers fix to demo-builder. Demo-builder should standardize to `editor@solodemo.law` or `admin@solo-law.demo` and document final credential.

5. **Testing baseline**: No `e2e/` scaffold or assertion list provided. Deploy-test node will need to write tests cold. Recommend demo-builder creates `e2e/playwright.config.ts` stub with the documented WebGPU flags so deploy-test can add assertions without setup overhead.

